526
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:10,360
Do you mind
if I wait?

527
00:35:20,760 --> 00:35:23,400
Hey.

528
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:26,440
Sir, sir.

529
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:28,559
Sir.

530
00:35:28,559 --> 00:35:30,880
Sir, sir.

531
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:55,880
Terry.

532
00:35:55,880 --> 00:35:57,519
It's time, Arlen.

533
00:35:57,519 --> 00:36:00,119
No.

534
00:36:01,639 --> 00:36:03,800
It is not time.
No, it isn't.

535
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:06,320
You promised me
a foreword.

536
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:08,480
I already sent you
something.

537
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:09,639
Yes, you did.

538
00:36:09,639 --> 00:36:12,599
You wrote, "get your own
imaginary friend,"

539
00:36:12,599 --> 00:36:15,920
followed by a multiple-choice
question about Tom Selleck.

540
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:19,519
Write whatever you want
and I'll sign it.

541
00:36:19,519 --> 00:36:23,719
Listen, you have 10%
of the God market... 10%.

542
00:36:23,719 --> 00:36:27,280
And I, the only person
alive who loves you,

543
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:29,480
am asking you to write
a couple of pages

544
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:33,320
about the book that you,
Arlen, wrote about him... God.

545
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:35,760
I've said
all I can say.

546
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:39,079
Arlen, we have let you out
of every responsibility...

547
00:36:39,079 --> 00:36:42,519
every appearance, every book
signing for the last 20 years.

548
00:36:42,519 --> 00:36:45,800
All we are asking is that you write
a couple of pages on the subject.

549
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,920
What is so hard
about that?

550
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:50,440
Try it sometime
and find out.

551
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:04,039
I've been
thinking it over

552
00:37:04,039 --> 00:37:05,559
and I want to give you
my phone number.

553
00:37:08,559 --> 00:37:09,719
I have a boyfriend.

554
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:14,199
Not for you.

555
00:37:14,199 --> 00:37:17,480
In case you guys are too busy and
have to cancel an appointment.

556
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:18,880
That's the reason.

557
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,719
Do you really
have a boyfriend?

558
00:37:30,719 --> 00:37:31,960
No.

559
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:35,639
If you did, would you want
to go on walks with him?

560
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:38,679
Yes.

561
00:37:38,679 --> 00:37:41,440
Good.

562
00:37:47,239 --> 00:37:49,599
Hey, you want
to walk around?

563
00:38:00,079 --> 00:38:01,639
Another day,

564
00:38:01,639 --> 00:38:03,719
another stroll
with a famous author.

565
00:38:03,719 --> 00:38:05,119
Must be exhausting.

566
00:38:05,119 --> 00:38:07,400
Oh, you have no idea.

567
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:14,920
I hope we're not breaking
some doctor-patient rule here.

568
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:17,000
No, it's part
of the service.

569
00:38:19,960 --> 00:38:22,679
No, I only have
three rules:

570
00:38:22,679 --> 00:38:25,639
Don't take advice from someone
you wouldn't trade places with;

571
00:38:25,639 --> 00:38:27,639
try not to do something
you can't take back;

572
00:38:27,639 --> 00:38:32,039
and something is what it is
and it's not something else.

573
00:38:32,039 --> 00:38:33,639
I forget my rule,
but I think

574
00:38:33,639 --> 00:38:35,679
it has something to do
with square dancing.

575
00:38:41,039 --> 00:38:43,960
Well, this is a street
I probably won't live on.

576
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:45,880
Oh, you never know.
Anything can happen.

577
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,800
Yeah. In the meantime,
looking's free.

578
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:50,599
Well, you know
what he says.

579
00:38:50,599 --> 00:38:54,440
No, I sure don't.

580
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:57,320
"For you and you alone
I have made this place

581
00:38:57,320 --> 00:39:00,519
kaleidoscope with wonder
to keep your eye upon

582
00:39:00,519 --> 00:39:02,960
as I turn, turn
the world."

583
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:06,880
Hmm, I don't remember that
from the book.

584
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:15,000
# Beautiful dreamer #

585
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:18,400
# wake unto me #

586
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:21,800
# starlight and dewdrops #

587
00:39:21,800 --> 00:39:24,519
# are waiting for thee... #

588
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:34,920
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

589
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:36,960
Do you know where
Arlen Faber lives?

590
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:38,239
I do.

591
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:43,079
- 2032, five blocks down.
- Thanks.

592
00:39:43,079 --> 00:39:45,519
- He threw water on my family.
- I'm sorry, what?

593
00:39:45,519 --> 00:39:49,280
We were singing the hymn and he
threw a bucket of water on us.

594
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:51,719
Be careful with him.

595
00:39:51,719 --> 00:39:54,519
Maybe he wrote "Me and God,"
but he did not read it.

596
00:40:05,199 --> 00:40:07,039
So you're Arlen Faber.

597
00:40:07,039 --> 00:40:10,000
You had no idea I'd be
this handsome, did you?

598
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:11,199
- I really liked your book.
- I know.

599
00:40:11,199 --> 00:40:13,400
But I need to be straight
with you right now.

600
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:14,639
Shoot.

601
00:40:14,639 --> 00:40:16,440
I can't accept any more
books right now.

602
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,400
And it seems you really
want to get rid of some books.

603
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:19,960
Oh, you noticed,
did you?

604
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:22,000
I'm willing
to make you a deal.

605
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:24,119
I could use a little
advice every now and then,

606
00:40:24,119 --> 00:40:26,280
even from someone
as obviously crazy as yourself.

607
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:28,360
So here's
what I propose:

608
00:40:28,360 --> 00:40:30,039
I'll let you trade me
books for questions.

609
00:40:30,039 --> 00:40:31,960
I have a question...

610
00:40:31,960 --> 00:40:33,639
can you guess how much
I hate this idea?

611
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:36,800
More than you would hate

612
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:39,119
every single new-age
sandal-wearing

613
00:40:39,119 --> 00:40:41,800
yoga-practicing fanatic
who walks into my store

614
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:42,960
knowing where you live?

615
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:47,000
Come on, just
three books per visit...

616
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:49,079
no one knows
where you live,

617
00:40:49,079 --> 00:40:50,440
Except for the guy
whose family you drenched.

618
00:41:04,440 --> 00:41:07,159
Five books, and you
don't get to argue with me.

619
00:41:07,159 --> 00:41:09,199
You ask, I answer.
That's it.

620
00:41:09,199 --> 00:41:11,480
- Deal.
- Now if we have completed

621
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:13,840
our little Faustian bargain, I would
like to go back inside

622
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:15,079
and weep for the life
I used to have.

623
00:41:15,079 --> 00:41:18,719
- I didn't get to ask you...
- Yes, you did.

624
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:28,679
So how are you today?

625
00:41:28,679 --> 00:41:31,599
Good good.
A little stiff, but better.

626
00:41:31,599 --> 00:41:33,639
You?

627
00:41:33,639 --> 00:41:36,559
I'm great,
really really great.

628
00:41:36,559 --> 00:41:38,519
Yeah?
And why is that?

629
00:41:38,519 --> 00:41:40,320
My son got a 4
on his paper yesterday

630
00:41:40,320 --> 00:41:43,039
And he feels
really great.

631
00:41:43,039 --> 00:41:45,000
What happened to an "A"?

632
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:47,360
Why isn't a 1 perfect?
A 4?

633
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:49,280
I have no idea.

634
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:51,159
Okay, and on three.

635
00:41:51,159 --> 00:41:54,599
One, two, three.

636
00:41:54,599 --> 00:41:58,199
Oh! Ahh.

637
00:41:58,199 --> 00:42:00,039
Would you like
to meet him?

638
00:42:02,679 --> 00:42:04,599
Alex, this is
my friend Arlen.

639
00:42:04,599 --> 00:42:06,519
Arlen, this is Alex.

640
00:42:06,519 --> 00:42:08,920
Word on the street is
you got a 4.

641
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:10,920
- Any truth to that?
- Yes.

642
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:13,800
- Well, congratulations.
- Thank you.

643
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:15,719
- It's nice meeting you.
- Nice meeting you.

644
00:42:18,039 --> 00:42:20,000
I'll be right back.

645
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:25,400
A great kid.

646
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:27,360
Yeah? Thanks.

647
00:42:27,360 --> 00:42:29,920
You want to know
something cool

648
00:42:29,920 --> 00:42:31,599
About shaking hands
with little people?

649
00:42:31,599 --> 00:42:33,760
Uh, okay.

650
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:35,880
They see us shaking hands,
but they don't know

651
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,800
that we squeeze
the other person's hand.

652
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:40,559
So they just hold hands
with you for a couple of seconds.

653
00:42:40,559 --> 00:42:43,119
- That is cool.
- Yeah yeah, it really is.

654
00:42:46,079 --> 00:42:48,360
See you soon.

655
00:42:58,679 --> 00:43:01,400
Hey.

656
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,719
Why is everybody
shaking my hand?

657
00:43:15,239 --> 00:43:17,159
Why can't I do
the things I want to do?

658
00:43:17,159 --> 00:43:19,079
There's so much I know
I'm capable of

659
00:43:19,079 --> 00:43:21,000
that I never actually do.
Why is that?

660
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:23,159
The trick is to realize that you're
always doing what you want to do...

661
00:43:23,159 --> 00:43:24,840
always.

662
00:43:24,840 --> 00:43:26,760
Nobody's making you
do anything.

663
00:43:26,760 --> 00:43:28,679
Once you get that,
you see that you're free

664
00:43:28,679 --> 00:43:30,920
and that life is really
just a series of choices.

665
00:43:30,920 --> 00:43:33,480
Nothing happens to you.
You choose.

666
00:43:40,280 --> 00:43:42,039
There's seven books here.

667
00:43:42,039 --> 00:43:44,679
A pre-coffee penalty...
two extra books.

668
00:43:49,119 --> 00:43:50,760
If God made everything,

669
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:52,840
then why are
some things bad,

670
00:43:52,840 --> 00:43:55,280
like, for example, the whole
pain-and-suffering thing?

671
00:43:55,280 --> 00:43:56,760
Opposites...

672
00:43:56,760 --> 00:43:59,719
without things that suck, you would have
no idea what good was

673
00:43:59,719 --> 00:44:01,320
and therefore would be
directionless.

674
00:44:01,320 --> 00:44:03,360
You smell shit,
and you walk the other way.

675
00:44:18,119 --> 00:44:20,840
Do I have a destiny,
or is it all free will?

676
00:44:22,199 --> 00:44:24,159
Destiny or free will?

677
00:44:24,159 --> 00:44:27,480
Free will... moving toward
or away from a purpose.

678
00:44:41,239 --> 00:44:43,159
Hello, "straighten up"
healing center.

679
00:44:43,159 --> 00:44:45,079
This is Arlen.

680
00:44:45,079 --> 00:44:47,559
Elizabeth, I felt
that our walk was

681
00:44:47,559 --> 00:44:50,280
Too short the other day.
I asked you to go for a walk.

682
00:44:50,280 --> 00:44:52,199
Perhaps it wasn't
as long as it should be

683
00:44:52,199 --> 00:44:54,440
when someone asks
for that.

684
00:44:54,440 --> 00:44:57,519
I don't usually
go for walks with people.

685
00:44:57,519 --> 00:44:59,679
I forget the protocol.

686
00:44:59,679 --> 00:45:01,599
What the
hell am I talking about?

687
00:45:01,599 --> 00:45:03,519
I know there's no
walk protocol per se.

688
00:45:03,519 --> 00:45:05,639
I mean, what would that be?
What could it be?

689
00:45:05,639 --> 00:45:07,280
Fuck. Fuck!

690
00:45:07,280 --> 00:45:09,760
You know, I hate answering
machines. For this very reason.

691
00:45:09,760 --> 00:45:12,360
They're like life... you can't
take anything back.

692
00:45:14,079 --> 00:45:16,639
I would like to go out with
you. I would like to go out with you.

693
00:45:16,639 --> 00:45:18,960
Did I already say that?
Tomorrow night.

694
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:21,480
And I hope
you will call me back

695
00:45:21,480 --> 00:45:23,400
on my phone...

696
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:26,159
the one here
at my home.

697
00:45:26,159 --> 00:45:28,679
Fuck.

698
00:45:28,679 --> 00:45:30,599
That was weird.

699
00:45:32,159 --> 00:45:33,880
Play it again.

700
00:45:35,559 --> 00:45:38,239
Are you ready
to take control of your life?

701
00:45:38,239 --> 00:45:39,880
Yes.

702
00:45:39,880 --> 00:45:42,119
There is one
who has all the answers.

703
00:45:42,119 --> 00:45:44,039
All you have to do
is ask.

704
00:45:44,039 --> 00:45:47,159
Ask. Ask.

705
00:45:47,159 --> 00:45:50,840
I want her
to like me, but...

706
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:53,360
Peace is your birthright.

707
00:45:53,360 --> 00:45:55,559
Ask and you shall receive.

708
00:45:55,559 --> 00:45:56,800
Stop interrupting.

709
00:45:56,800 --> 00:45:59,159
Wisdom is like
a fox in winter.

710
00:45:59,159 --> 00:46:01,440
And the ice is
where he dances.

711
00:46:12,159 --> 00:46:14,440
Kris, listen,
I gotta go.

712
00:46:14,440 --> 00:46:16,360
I don't have time
to tell you why we dream

713
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:18,559
or help you manifest
sanity. Maybe tomorrow.

714
00:46:18,559 --> 00:46:21,119
I'm trying to stay sober
and my dad won't stop drinking.

715
00:46:21,119 --> 00:46:23,320
How can I love him even though
he's selfish and he's scaring me?

716
00:46:24,679 --> 00:46:27,719
Um,

717
00:46:27,719 --> 00:46:29,079
that's hard.

718
00:46:31,000 --> 00:46:35,440
I guess what's getting in the way
are your expectations...

719
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:37,960
If he would do "x",
then you'd be happy.

720
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:40,599
It doesn't work
that way.

721
00:46:40,599 --> 00:46:42,320
I think you have to
let go of that

722
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:44,239
and maybe what you want
will happen

723
00:46:44,239 --> 00:46:45,840
and maybe it won't.

724
00:46:45,840 --> 00:46:47,480
Either way,
you're better off.

725
00:46:50,039 --> 00:46:51,880
And you should go
to A.A. Meetings.

726
00:46:53,559 --> 00:46:56,239
- It's hard.
- Yes, it is.

727
00:47:00,239 --> 00:47:01,719
So you want to give me
some books or something?

728
00:47:03,199 --> 00:47:06,079
Oh, twice as many
next time.

729
00:47:08,519 --> 00:47:10,440
I'm sorry about
when we met...

730
00:47:10,440 --> 00:47:13,760
the lap-dancing-
piercing-festival comment.

731
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:15,480
I didn't know you were
having such a hard time.

732
00:47:16,920 --> 00:47:19,480
So you're only awful
to people that don't have problems.

733
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:21,320
It's good to know.

734
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:33,000
I'm ready to take control of my life.

735
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:35,760
I'm ready to take
control of my life.

736
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:38,639
I'm ready
to take control...

737
00:47:41,239 --> 00:47:43,159
Of my life.

738
00:47:51,360 --> 00:47:54,480
I thought I heard you out
here. What are you doing?

739
00:47:54,480 --> 00:47:57,079
Uh, stretching.
I was...

740
00:47:57,079 --> 00:48:00,159
I always stretch
before I knock.

741
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:03,400
Anne, we're going.

742
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:10,559
- Hi, Arlen.
- Hi, Alex.

743
00:48:12,480 --> 00:48:14,199
Hi, Anne.

744
00:48:14,199 --> 00:48:16,360
- You wear a lot of hats.
- Yeah.

745
00:48:16,360 --> 00:48:19,559
- Okay, be good for Annie.
- Okay.

746
00:48:19,559 --> 00:48:22,199
Mommy will give you a kiss when
she gets home. It won't be too late.

747
00:48:22,199 --> 00:48:25,119
You know what to do. No sweets tonight,
okay? Just popcorn.

748
00:48:25,119 --> 00:48:27,320
Call me if you need
anything. Use the fruit spray.

749
00:48:27,320 --> 00:48:30,480
- There's light bulbs.
- You're freaking out.

750
00:48:30,480 --> 00:48:32,880
Can he tell?

751
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:34,960
- Not yet.
- Not yet what?

752
00:48:34,960 --> 00:48:37,239
Nothing.

753
00:48:37,239 --> 00:48:39,559
And there's just a few
more things I put down for you...

754
00:48:39,559 --> 00:48:42,199
- Just a few.
- I've done this before.

755
00:48:42,199 --> 00:48:44,519
I love you, baby.
Mm, I love you.

756
00:48:44,519 --> 00:48:46,440
- I love you too, mom.
- I love you. Okay.

757
00:48:46,440 --> 00:48:48,360
I love you.
I love you.

758
00:48:48,360 --> 00:48:51,400
- Mwah!
- Have fun.

759
00:48:51,400 --> 00:48:53,760
The Air Force should be dropping
off supplies in the next couple of days.

760
00:48:53,760 --> 00:48:55,239
So see if you can
hold on till then.

761
00:49:04,920 --> 00:49:07,480
You look beautiful.

762
00:49:07,480 --> 00:49:09,440
Thank you.

763
00:49:10,440 --> 00:49:13,360
Take me out, Arlen.

764
00:49:38,119 --> 00:49:40,519
This is nice.

765
00:49:40,519 --> 00:49:43,000
I bet this is where you take
all your chiropractors.

766
00:49:43,000 --> 00:49:44,599
Is it obvious?

767
00:49:46,880 --> 00:49:49,119
So how did you come to be
the angel of alignment?

768
00:49:51,280 --> 00:49:55,079
Well, I needed
to start over.

769
00:49:55,079 --> 00:49:57,239
I needed a change.

770
00:49:57,239 --> 00:49:59,880
And I liked
the immediacy of it.

771
00:49:59,880 --> 00:50:02,760
People walk in,
or crawl in, hurt,

772
00:50:02,760 --> 00:50:05,400
And when they leave
they feel better, and I did it.

773
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:07,480
- And the legend is born.
- Oh.

774
00:50:07,480 --> 00:50:10,039
What good are the gifts we
have if we don't share them?

775
00:50:10,039 --> 00:50:12,440
I like that we have that
in common.

776
00:50:13,960 --> 00:50:15,880
To a great chiropractor.

777
00:50:15,880 --> 00:50:19,559
To a great...

778
00:50:19,559 --> 00:50:23,159
transcriber of thoughts
from outer space.

779
00:50:27,039 --> 00:50:29,320
Tell me about Alexander.

780
00:50:29,320 --> 00:50:31,559
Alex.
He hates "A lexander."

781
00:50:31,559 --> 00:50:33,360
Alex.

782
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:34,800
He's great.
He's a great kid.

783
00:50:34,800 --> 00:50:38,079
He keeps me together
just by being around, you know?

784
00:50:38,079 --> 00:50:40,280
How often does he see
his dad?

785
00:50:43,039 --> 00:50:45,199
Oh, well,

786
00:50:45,199 --> 00:50:48,760
he hasn't seen his father
in over three years.

787
00:50:48,760 --> 00:50:50,760
What happened?

788
00:50:55,880 --> 00:50:59,400
Alex's dad
was one of those guys

789
00:50:59,400 --> 00:51:01,639
who always has
a great new idea,

790
00:51:01,639 --> 00:51:04,960
and for a while
that was us.

791
00:51:04,960 --> 00:51:07,119
And then one day

792
00:51:07,119 --> 00:51:09,280
he took Alex
to the park

793
00:51:09,280 --> 00:51:12,719
and told him that he had
to go away for a little while,

794
00:51:12,719 --> 00:51:15,440
but he would be back
in two weeks... two weeks.

795
00:51:15,440 --> 00:51:17,559
And that turned into
three years.

796
00:51:17,559 --> 00:51:19,679
Alex was just so little

797
00:51:19,679 --> 00:51:22,679
that I hope he,
you know, forgot.

798
00:51:24,599 --> 00:51:26,480
Really, I should have
known better.

799
00:51:26,480 --> 00:51:28,199
- Oh, no.
- Are you okay?

800
00:51:28,199 --> 00:51:30,119
- Fuck no.
- Arlen?

801
00:51:30,119 --> 00:51:32,440
Don't move.

802
00:51:36,159 --> 00:51:38,079
If you don't stop
playing that song,

803
00:51:38,079 --> 00:51:40,519
I will chew
through my wrists.

804
00:51:49,400 --> 00:51:51,320
Where were we?

805
00:51:51,320 --> 00:51:54,599
I guess I was just boring you
with stories about my life.

806
00:51:54,599 --> 00:51:56,320
No no no, please.
I'm sorry.

807
00:51:56,320 --> 00:51:58,280
No, this is a nice place
and I'm bringing it down.

808
00:51:58,280 --> 00:51:59,639
No, I'm listening.

809
00:51:59,639 --> 00:52:01,800
He's listening.

810
00:52:05,119 --> 00:52:07,119
What do you want to hear?
You want to hear about

811
00:52:07,119 --> 00:52:09,719
How I'm so freaked out that
I'm not doing everything I can;

812
00:52:09,719 --> 00:52:11,639
That I'm so freaked out
all the time;

813
00:52:11,639 --> 00:52:14,639
That I'm afraid
that I'm not doing enough;

814
00:52:14,639 --> 00:52:17,320
And that that fear is turning me
into somebody I don't want to be

815
00:52:17,320 --> 00:52:19,719
and I can't stop it?
You have no idea what it's like

816
00:52:19,719 --> 00:52:22,559
to be pulled all the time...
I mean, not by Alex

817
00:52:22,559 --> 00:52:24,920
but by this idea
that I'm not doing enough;

818
00:52:24,920 --> 00:52:28,320
That I am not enough.

819
00:52:28,320 --> 00:52:31,559
He knows.

820
00:52:31,559 --> 00:52:33,480
And he wants you to know

821
00:52:33,480 --> 00:52:35,719
that you are enough
and so much more.

822
00:52:35,719 --> 00:52:40,199
You are here so God can experience
the world through your eyes,

823
00:52:40,199 --> 00:52:43,519
see what you see,
feel what you feel.

824
00:52:43,519 --> 00:52:46,159
Every day he can't wait

825
00:52:46,159 --> 00:52:48,679
to see what you'll do,

826
00:52:48,679 --> 00:52:50,760
what makes you laugh,
what moves you...

827
00:52:50,760 --> 00:52:53,760
He can't wait.
Every day through you

828
00:52:53,760 --> 00:52:56,880
He falls in love
with the world all over again.

829
00:52:59,559 --> 00:53:02,679
Elizabeth,
you are his muse.

830
00:53:09,960 --> 00:53:11,880
Thank you.

831
00:53:15,719 --> 00:53:18,960
Oh my God,
it's so beautiful.

832
00:53:18,960 --> 00:53:20,320
Yes, it is.

833
00:53:20,320 --> 00:53:22,559
I bet you have
some great parties here.

834
00:53:22,559 --> 00:53:25,599
Oh, no one has been
in here for five years.

835
00:53:27,239 --> 00:53:28,400
Five years?

836
00:53:28,400 --> 00:53:31,079
Since my father died.

837
00:53:31,079 --> 00:53:33,960
Oh, I'm sorry.

838
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:36,360
Me too.

839
00:53:39,239 --> 00:53:41,960
Don't touch that.

840
00:53:41,960 --> 00:53:43,800
I won't.

841
00:53:43,800 --> 00:53:46,480
Hey, I want
to show you something.

842
00:53:48,639 --> 00:53:50,559
Okay.

843
00:54:05,440 --> 00:54:06,760
This is my office.

844
00:54:06,760 --> 00:54:08,519
I know.
I saw the sign.

845
00:54:08,519 --> 00:54:10,119
Why are there
signs everywhere?

846
00:54:10,119 --> 00:54:12,039
Because my dad
had Alzheimer's

847
00:54:12,039 --> 00:54:14,760
and in the end it was hard
for him to remember things.

848
00:54:14,760 --> 00:54:16,920
So the signs helped
for a while.

849
00:54:22,920 --> 00:54:24,119
Ta-dah!

850
00:54:24,119 --> 00:54:26,000
- Wow.
- I kind of collect them.

851
00:54:26,000 --> 00:54:28,800
My dad and I used to watch
monster movies together.

852
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:30,360
And I kept the models
from when I was a kid.

853
00:54:30,360 --> 00:54:34,079
And over the years, you know,
I'd pick up another one at a garage sale

854
00:54:34,079 --> 00:54:36,360
or a science-fiction expo.

855
00:54:36,360 --> 00:54:38,760
I really like them.

856
00:54:38,760 --> 00:54:41,320
And I think I've got
a pretty good collection,

857
00:54:42,559 --> 00:54:44,360
If you like
that sort of thing.

858
00:54:44,360 --> 00:54:46,519
Maybe not.
It's not for everybody.

859
00:54:46,519 --> 00:54:48,559
It's dumb, I guess.
We should go.

860
00:54:48,559 --> 00:54:50,239
No, I love 'em.

861
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:54,719
I think
they're wonderful.

862
00:54:54,719 --> 00:54:56,679
- You do?
- Yeah.

863
00:54:58,239 --> 00:54:59,840
What are they doing
all crammed in here, though?

864
00:54:59,840 --> 00:55:02,679
You should put them out.
God knows you have the room.

865
00:55:02,679 --> 00:55:04,519
Where are you going?

866
00:55:10,079 --> 00:55:12,000
There, that's better.

867
00:55:12,000 --> 00:55:14,639
But I don't want it there. I want it
back with the other monsters.

868
00:55:14,639 --> 00:55:17,920
Okay, just try it out.

869
00:55:17,920 --> 00:55:19,679
Consider it an experiment.

870
00:55:22,079 --> 00:55:24,960
- Arlen.
- Hmm?

871
00:55:24,960 --> 00:55:26,719
Thank you
for bringing me here.

872
00:55:26,719 --> 00:55:28,480
Oh...

873
00:55:28,480 --> 00:55:30,599
You caught me
off-guard tonight.

874
00:55:30,599 --> 00:55:34,920
Tell me,
am I the first girl

875
00:55:34,920 --> 00:55:36,960
to see your monsters?

876
00:55:36,960 --> 00:55:38,239
I'm sorry.

877
00:55:38,239 --> 00:55:40,079
Just give me one second,
all right?

878
00:55:43,559 --> 00:55:45,480
Don't go away.

879
00:55:48,119 --> 00:55:50,480
I'm blowing it again,
aren't I?

880
00:55:52,199 --> 00:55:54,119
No, I love it

881
00:55:54,119 --> 00:55:55,519
when I'm about
to kiss someone

882
00:55:55,519 --> 00:55:57,760
and they leave me
to protect a plastic toy.

883
00:55:59,880 --> 00:56:02,760
But...

884
00:56:02,760 --> 00:56:05,159
a kiss is
so much better

885
00:56:05,159 --> 00:56:07,159
knowing they're safe.

886
00:56:18,679 --> 00:56:21,519
I gotta just remember to let that shit
go, you know what I mean?

887
00:56:21,519 --> 00:56:25,079
It's just a car, right?
It's not life-or-death.

888
00:56:25,079 --> 00:56:27,719
Wasn't that long ago,
if somebody cut me off

889
00:56:27,719 --> 00:56:29,199
I'd go on
a three-day binge.

890
00:56:29,199 --> 00:56:33,280
And now I just pray
silently for their death.

891
00:56:38,880 --> 00:56:41,360
Hi, my name is Ross
and I'm an alcoholic.

892
00:56:41,360 --> 00:56:43,559
Hi, Ross.

893
00:56:43,559 --> 00:56:45,519
That's about all the time
that we have,

894
00:56:45,519 --> 00:56:48,039
unless anyone has
a burning desire.

895
00:56:49,199 --> 00:56:50,440
What about you...

896
00:56:50,440 --> 00:56:52,360
The newcomer?

897
00:56:56,320 --> 00:56:58,960
Fine. You want me
to say something?

898
00:57:00,239 --> 00:57:02,800
How about this?

899
00:57:02,800 --> 00:57:04,719
I fucking hate this.

900
00:57:04,719 --> 00:57:06,679
I fucking hate
that I have to be here.

901
00:57:06,679 --> 00:57:08,559
And I fucking hate
all of you

902
00:57:08,559 --> 00:57:09,840
and your pathetic
little stories.

903
00:57:09,840 --> 00:57:11,840
I can't believe
I've ended up here.

904
00:57:11,840 --> 00:57:15,159
It's fucked.
I'm fucked.

905
00:57:15,159 --> 00:57:16,760
And you're fucked too.

906
00:57:16,760 --> 00:57:19,119
- I hear that.
- I hear that.

907
00:57:19,119 --> 00:57:21,079
- I hear that too.
- Right on.

908
00:57:22,199 --> 00:57:24,119
Listen, I've got
a great plan.

909
00:57:24,119 --> 00:57:26,719
I think what I'll do is walk around
at night tripping the locals,

910
00:57:26,719 --> 00:57:28,639
throwing their backs
out of alignment.

911
00:57:28,639 --> 00:57:30,679
It's tough work,
but the war needs soldiers.

912
00:57:30,679 --> 00:57:34,920
Well, that sounds great.
When can you start?

913
00:57:34,920 --> 00:57:37,480
Good luck on the moon.
We always knew you could do it.

914
00:57:37,480 --> 00:57:39,199
Thanks.

915
00:57:41,519 --> 00:57:43,440
Gee, you think
he's gonna be safe?

916
00:57:43,440 --> 00:57:45,480
Are you
making fun of me?

917
00:57:45,480 --> 00:57:48,360
No, I was just making fun

918
00:57:48,360 --> 00:57:50,280
of that inquisition holdover
of a car seat.

919
00:57:50,280 --> 00:57:53,400
One more strap... I think
you could get him to confess.

920
00:57:53,400 --> 00:57:55,880
Keeps him safe.

921
00:57:58,159 --> 00:58:00,480
- Okay, I'll see you later.
- Yeah, mm-hmm.

922
00:58:11,320 --> 00:58:14,000
So what's the deal with
heaven and hell anyway?

923
00:58:14,000 --> 00:58:16,800
I've seen hell, and it's name is
Reno, Nevada.

924
00:58:20,760 --> 00:58:24,039
I can't believe God would
punish people for not believing in him.

925
00:58:24,039 --> 00:58:25,960
Ah, the rapture.

926
00:58:25,960 --> 00:58:27,880
What's that?

927
00:58:27,880 --> 00:58:30,440
Well, I like to think
of it as a monster movie.

928
00:58:30,440 --> 00:58:33,800
The monster destroys
some people and spares others.

929
00:58:33,800 --> 00:58:36,840
So who is the monster?

930
00:58:36,840 --> 00:58:38,760
God.

931
00:58:38,760 --> 00:58:41,239
God is the monster.

932
00:58:46,119 --> 00:58:48,639
Have you been to
the chiropractor recently?

933
00:58:48,639 --> 00:58:50,559
"Straighten up"
healing center...

934
00:58:50,559 --> 00:58:52,639
We'll heal you
as you straighten.

935
00:58:52,639 --> 00:58:54,000
No way.

936
00:58:54,000 --> 00:58:55,239
"Straighten up"
healing center.

937
00:58:55,239 --> 00:58:57,760
Have you been to
the chiropractor recently?

938
00:58:57,760 --> 00:59:00,079
What are you doing?

939
00:59:00,079 --> 00:59:02,480
Elizabeth said we needed
to get the word out.

940
00:59:02,480 --> 00:59:04,360
Nobody wants to talk
to a spine.

941
00:59:04,360 --> 00:59:06,239
We're offering
a discount.

942
00:59:06,239 --> 00:59:09,119
- A spine?
- I don't mind.

943
00:59:09,119 --> 00:59:10,519
"Straighten up"
healing center.

944
00:59:10,519 --> 00:59:13,199
- A spine?
- I don't mind.

945
00:59:13,199 --> 00:59:14,920
Bye, Mr. Mankowitz.
See you next week.

946
00:59:14,920 --> 00:59:17,039
We're a new business.
We have to advertise.

947
00:59:17,039 --> 00:59:19,320
Is that helping
your business?

948
00:59:19,320 --> 00:59:20,320
Oh, no.

949
00:59:22,400 --> 00:59:23,960
Honey, how did
that happen?

950
00:59:23,960 --> 00:59:25,880
- We got you.
- Hang in there, Anne.

951
00:59:25,880 --> 00:59:28,360
We've got a bone saw
around here somewhere.

952
00:59:28,360 --> 00:59:30,360
That's so funny.

953
00:59:30,360 --> 00:59:32,000
Honey, we'll get you
out of it.

954
00:59:32,000 --> 00:59:33,960
- Oh.
- Oh, no. Are you okay?

955
00:59:33,960 --> 00:59:36,320
- I'll go home.
- Go home now?

956
00:59:36,320 --> 00:59:38,639
- Well, that sucked.
- Oh, no.

957
00:59:38,639 --> 00:59:42,480
I'm so sorry.
Are you coming back?

958
00:59:42,480 --> 00:59:44,960
Do you want me
to call you later?

959
00:59:44,960 --> 00:59:48,559
What are we
gonna do with you?

960
00:59:48,559 --> 00:59:49,920
I can take him
to the park.

961
00:59:49,920 --> 00:59:51,840
- Okay.
- No, that's okay.

962
00:59:51,840 --> 00:59:53,760
It's more complicated
than you think.

963
00:59:53,760 --> 00:59:55,800
I can take a kid
to a park.

964
00:59:55,800 --> 00:59:58,320
Right.

965
00:59:58,320 --> 01:00:00,239
- Wanna do that?
- Yes.

966
01:00:00,239 --> 01:00:01,440
Yes?

967
01:00:01,440 --> 01:00:03,360
- Okay, go to the park.
- Come on.

968
01:00:03,360 --> 01:00:05,480
Just to the park, though,
right? Be careful.

969
01:00:05,480 --> 01:00:07,760
I mean, have fun.
Be careful.

970
01:00:08,880 --> 01:00:10,800
Just the park.
Have fun.

971
01:00:12,960 --> 01:00:15,880
I don't ever want
to step on a nail.

972
01:00:15,880 --> 01:00:18,440
Got it.

973
01:00:21,480 --> 01:00:25,159
In your house, do you
have a favorite towel?

974
01:00:25,159 --> 01:00:26,800
Yes.

975
01:00:29,800 --> 01:00:31,719
I can read
upside down.

976
01:00:35,760 --> 01:00:38,199
Hey, I got something
for you.

977
01:00:44,679 --> 01:00:46,960
It's a proper vehicle

978
01:00:46,960 --> 01:00:49,199
For future missions.

979
01:00:52,639 --> 01:00:54,559
What are you waiting for?
Go play already.

980
01:00:54,559 --> 01:00:56,280
- Can I?
- Yeah, get out of here.

981
01:01:03,039 --> 01:01:05,000
I don't really have
a favorite towel.

982
01:01:05,000 --> 01:01:07,400
Me neither.

983
01:01:13,199 --> 01:01:15,039
Bring it in.
Bring it in.

984
01:01:15,039 --> 01:01:16,960
That's it.
Come on.

985
01:01:16,960 --> 01:01:19,320
Circle the airport.
Circle the airport.

986
01:01:19,320 --> 01:01:22,800
That's it.
Bring it in.

987
01:01:28,760 --> 01:01:30,480
Kris, now is
not a good time.

988
01:01:30,480 --> 01:01:33,159
My dad died today.

989
01:01:33,159 --> 01:01:35,280
Hi.

990
01:01:35,280 --> 01:01:37,920
- My dad died today.
- Oh my God.

991
01:01:37,920 --> 01:01:39,840
I didn't know where else to
go, so I just came here.

992
01:01:39,840 --> 01:01:41,440
I know it's not
our regular time,

993
01:01:41,440 --> 01:01:43,440
So you can give me some extra
books if you want to.

994
01:01:43,440 --> 01:01:44,719
- What's he talking about?
- Nothing. Kris,

995
01:01:44,719 --> 01:01:46,480
now is not a good time.

996
01:01:46,480 --> 01:01:48,599
I'm thirsty.

997
01:01:48,599 --> 01:01:50,519
Yeah, Arlen, get him
something to drink.

998
01:01:50,519 --> 01:01:52,440
Sure.

999
01:01:53,679 --> 01:01:55,599
I've never been in here.

1000
01:01:55,599 --> 01:01:58,079
- The place is huge.
- It is.

1001
01:01:58,079 --> 01:02:00,000
He's got nice stuff.

1002
01:02:07,880 --> 01:02:10,119
Thanks.

1003
01:02:16,239 --> 01:02:19,079
So I came home
and I found him.

1004
01:02:19,079 --> 01:02:21,679
He was sitting
at the table

1005
01:02:21,679 --> 01:02:23,840
doing a crossword puzzle.

1006
01:02:23,840 --> 01:02:25,559
He never does
crossword puzzles.

1007
01:02:25,559 --> 01:02:27,480
Kris just got out
of rehab.

1008
01:02:29,519 --> 01:02:31,679
Oh.
Are you okay?

1009
01:02:32,960 --> 01:02:35,480
Hey, let's not talk.
Let's just sit here.

1010
01:02:35,480 --> 01:02:37,719
That's a good idea.

1011
01:02:40,559 --> 01:02:43,119
What did you mean
about extra books?

1012
01:02:43,119 --> 01:02:45,800
I own a little bookstore...
"Book Trader."

1013
01:02:45,800 --> 01:02:47,320
Oh, yeah, that's where
I bought your book.

1014
01:02:47,320 --> 01:02:48,800
Perfect.

1015
01:02:48,800 --> 01:02:51,159
Arlen tried to sell me back
some books and I couldn't afford it.

1016
01:02:51,159 --> 01:02:53,039
So he freaked out.
And now I come to his house

1017
01:02:53,039 --> 01:02:54,840
and exchange books
for questions.

1018
01:02:54,840 --> 01:02:57,159
You make him pay for his
questions with books?

1019
01:02:57,159 --> 01:02:59,159
- Totally fair.
- No, it's not. It's awful.

1020
01:02:59,159 --> 01:03:01,559
You haven't heard
the questions.

1021
01:03:01,559 --> 01:03:03,480
Arlen, I can't
feel anything...

1022
01:03:03,480 --> 01:03:04,800
Nothing.

1023
01:03:04,800 --> 01:03:06,679
I should be able
to feel something, shouldn't I?

1024
01:03:16,079 --> 01:03:20,800
Do you like
working at the bookstore?

1025
01:03:20,800 --> 01:03:21,880
I love the bookstore...

1026
01:03:21,880 --> 01:03:25,519
All those ideas
somebody cared enough about

1027
01:03:25,519 --> 01:03:27,440
To put all that
work into.

1028
01:03:27,440 --> 01:03:29,519
I could never do
anything like that.

1029
01:03:29,519 --> 01:03:32,679
Sometimes I'll just stand in
the middle of the store at night

1030
01:03:32,679 --> 01:03:35,639
and imagine that all those
authors are surrounding me.

1031
01:03:35,639 --> 01:03:39,679
